* pdfout
Fast PDF modification and analysis tool based on the [[http://mupdf.com/][mupdf library]] and the [[http://yaml.org/][YAML data serialization standard]].

pdfout can
 - dump and modify outlines, page labels, keys of the information dictionary
 - extract text
 - repair broken cross-reference tables

** Install  

*** install prequisites

*dpkg-based: e.g. Trisquel, Debian*
 : $ apt-get install gcc make pkg-config libyaml-dev libunistring-dev libssl-dev
*rpm-based: e.g. Fedora*
 : $ dnf install tar pkgconfig gcc make libyaml-devel libunistring-devel openssl-devel

*Cygwin*

run the setup*.exe and select the packages =gcc-core, make, pkg-config, libyaml-devel, libunistring2, libunistring-devel, openssl-devel=

*** download and build
for md5 and gpg signatures see [[http://amba.github.io/index.html]]
#+BEGIN_EXAMPLE
 $ wget amba.github.io/pdfout-0.1-alpha.tar.gz
 $ tar -xzf pdfout-0.1.tar.gz
 $ cd pdfout-0.1
 $ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local
 $ make
 $ make install
#+END_EXAMPLE

Now run
: $ pdfout --describe-commands
to list the available subcommands.
